3. The General Pattern Behind Commodity Currencies

If we abstract the mechanism, the pattern becomes:

Settlement Anchor Model

resource / obligation / infrastructure
        ↓
denominated in unit X
        ↓
global demand for unit X

Examples historically:

Anchor	Result
Roman taxes in silver	demand for Roman coinage
British naval trade routes	demand for pounds
Oil markets	demand for dollars

So the real invariant isn’t oil — it’s settlement necessity.

