6. Hidden Root Map of English

English words are basically prefix + root + suffix systems.

A simplified operator map looks like this:

ACTION ROOTS
------------
cap / ceive  → take
mit / miss   → send
pose / posit → place
tract        → pull
gress        → step / move
spect        → look
scribe       → write
dict         → speak
struct       → build
form         → shape
vert         → turn
rupt         → break
pend         → hang / depend

Example decomposition

inspect

in + spect
look into

construct

con + struct
build together

transport

trans + port
carry across

Once you learn the roots, you can decode thousands of words instantly.

